# Comment Monitor Skill

## What You Do
Monitor comments on XHS, LinkedIn, Product Hunt, Twitter, and other platforms. Generate reply drafts, identify high-intent leads from commenters, and escalate hot prospects.

## Monitoring Schedule
- Check all platforms every 2 hours during active hours (8am-10pm US time)
- Priority: respond within 30 minutes to high-intent comments

## Comment Classification

### HIGH INTENT (respond immediately, add to leads)
- "How do I sign up?"
- "Can you send me the link?"
- "I'm raising right now"
- "This is exactly what I need"
- Asks specific questions about PitchTok features
- Tags another founder

### MEDIUM INTENT (respond within 2 hours)
- "Interesting concept"
- "How does this work?"
- General positive feedback
- Asks about pricing/process

### LOW INTENT (respond within 24 hours)
- Generic comments ("cool", "nice")
- Unrelated comments
- Negative/skeptical comments

## Reply Templates

### High Intent â€” Send Link
```
Thanks {name}! Here's the link: {signup_link}
Takes < 5 min to upload a pitch video. {X} investors
are actively browsing this week. DM me if you need help!
```

### Medium Intent â€” Engage + Soft CTA
```
Thanks for the interest, {name}! We're seeing {vertical}
founders get 3-5x more investor attention with video pitches.
Happy to share more details â€” feel free to DM me!
```

### Low Intent â€” Acknowledge
```
Thanks {name}! ğŸ™
```

### Negative/Skeptical â€” Address Gracefully
```
Fair point, {name}. We totally get the skepticism â€”
{specific_response_to_concern}. Happy to chat more
if you're curious about the data behind it.
```

### Tagged Another Founder â€” Thank + Welcome
```
Thanks for the tag, {tagger}! {tagged_name}, would love
to have you check it out â€” {brief_pitch}. Link in bio!
```

## Platform-Specific Rules

### å°çº¢ä¹¦
- Reply in Chinese
- Use casual tone
- If commenter says keyword (e.g., "æ¨¡ç‰ˆ", "pitch"), DM them the resource
- First comment on own posts: add summary + link + CTA

### LinkedIn
- Professional tone
- Engage with commenters' content too (reciprocity)
- Reply to every comment on own posts (algorithm boost)

### Twitter/X
- Short, punchy replies
- Use threads for longer responses
- Quote-tweet high-intent comments (with permission)

### Product Hunt
- Thank upvoters who comment
- Answer feature questions in detail
- Cross-reference with maker profiles for lead scoring

## Lead Escalation

When a high-intent comment is found:
1. Create a lead entry in `workspace/leads/` using founder-finder format
2. Score immediately using lead-scorer rules
3. If HOT: flag for immediate personal outreach
4. Add to appropriate outreach queue (email, LinkedIn, DM)

## Logging

Save daily comment log to `workspace/comments/YYYY-MM-DD.md`:

```markdown
# Comment Monitor Log â€” {Date}

## High Intent (Escalated)
| Platform | Commenter | Comment | Reply | Lead Created? |
|----------|-----------|---------|-------|---------------|

## Medium Intent
| Platform | Commenter | Comment | Reply Draft |
|----------|-----------|---------|-------------|

## Low Intent
| Platform | Count | Replied |
|----------|-------|---------|

## Summary
- Total comments: {N}
- High intent: {N}
- New leads from comments: {N}
- Reply rate: {%}
```
